flowRoot.flowPara: The Liferay Portal Administrator's Guide is your complete guide to installing, integrating, configuring, and maintaining a Liferay Portal server. This comprehensive guide will show you how to bring up a Liferay Portal server and keep it running. From installing a bundle to configuring a Liferay cluster, every aspect of running Liferay Portal is covered.
Whether you have experience with Liferay Portal or not, this book contains the information you need to keep your portal environment running smoothly.
Configuring a Bundle for an Enterprise
Installing Liferay on Your Application Server
Making Liferay Coexist with Other Java EE Applications
Rich Sezov is Knowledge Manager and a Senior Engineer for Liferay, Inc. He has been building portals for Fortune 500 companies and non-profits since 2003.
Complete instructions for installing and maintaining Liferay Portal
Services Oriented Architecture with Liferay Portal
Integration with LDAP, Single Sign-On, Workflow, and Chat services
